SystemTray-Applet-Gnome

SystemTray::Applet allows you to create simple system tray applets without
caring about the exact windowing interface the user users. Currently
gnome and the command line are supported. SystemTary::Applet::Gnome implements GNOME
support.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc SystemTray::Applet::Gnome

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=SystemTray-Applet-Gnome

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/SystemTray-Applet-Gnome

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/SystemTray-Applet-Gnome

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/SystemTray-Applet-Gnome


